This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on July 20, 2018. The memorandum is addressed to the Secretary of State and the Secretary of Defense and concerns the continuation of U.S. drug interdiction assistance to the government of Colombia. The President certifies that the interdiction of aircraft suspected of engaging in illicit drug trafficking in Colombia's airspace is necessary due to the significant threat posed by drug trafficking to the country's national security. The President also states that Colombia has appropriate procedures in place to protect against innocent loss of life during such interdiction efforts. The Secretary of State is instructed to publish this determination in the Federal Register and notify Congress accordingly.